            <fr:title text="Nerode congruence">Nerode congruence</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  Given a language <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}]]></fr:tex> over the alphabet <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex>, two words <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x, y \in  \Sigma ^*]]></fr:tex> are <html:strong>Nerode congruent</html:strong> if for any word <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[xz \in  \mathcal {L}]]></fr:tex> iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[yz \in  \mathcal {L}]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
